quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,136,"Then We destroyed the others."
  37,137,"And indeed, you pass by them in the morning"
  37,138,"And at night. Then will you not use reason?"
  40,79,"It is Allāh who made for you the grazing animals upon which you ride, and some of them you eat."
  40,80,"And for you therein are [other] benefits and that you may realize upon them a need which is in your breasts;{1} and upon them and upon ships you are carried.",footnotes:1:[i.e., that you may use the animals to carry your loads to distant places, according to need.]
  40,81,"And He shows you His signs. So which of the signs of Allāh do you deny?"
  42,43,"And whoever is patient and forgives - indeed, that is of the matters [worthy] of resolve.{1}",footnotes:1:[On the part of those seeking the reward of Allāh.]
  42,44,"And he whom Allāh sends astray - for him there is no protector beyond Him. And you will see the wrongdoers, when they see the punishment, saying, "
  42,45,"And you will see them being exposed to it [i.e., the Fire], humbled from humiliation, looking from [behind] a covert glance. And those who had believed will say, "
  43,25,"So We took retribution from them; then see how was the end of the deniers."
  43,26,"And [mention, O Muḥammad], when Abraham said to his father and his people, "
  43,27,"Except for He who created me; and indeed, He will guide me."
  44,10,"Then watch for the Day when the sky will bring a visible smoke"
  44,11,"Covering the people; this is a painful torment."
  44,12,"[They will say], "
  45,1,"Ḥā, Meem.{1}",footnotes:1:[See footnote to 2:1.]
  45,2,"The revelation of the Book is from Allāh, the Exalted in Might, the Wise."
  45,3,"Indeed, within the heavens and earth are signs for the believers."